<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Cosmos1-2006-2.jpg" class="image" title="An artist's depiction of a Cosmos 1 type spaceship in orbit"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/62/Cosmos1-2006-2.jpg/180px-Cosmos1-2006-2.jpg" width="180" height="135" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Cosmos1-2006-2.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
An artist's depiction of a Cosmos 1 type spaceship in orbit</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Solar sails</b> (also called <b><a href="/wiki/Light" title="Light">light</a> sails</b> or <b><a href="/wiki/Photon" title="Photon">photon</a> sails</b>) are a form of <a href="/wiki/Spacecraft_propulsion" title="Spacecraft propulsion">spacecraft propulsion</a> that uses the <a href="/wiki/Radiation_pressure" title="Radiation pressure">pressure</a> of <a href="/wiki/Light" title="Light">light</a> from a <a href="/wiki/Star" title="Star">star</a> or <a href="/wiki/Laser" title="Laser">laser</a> to push enormous <a href="/wiki/Membrane_mirror" title="Membrane mirror">ultra-thin mirrors</a> to high speeds.</p>
