<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Solar_sail&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/smallsats/nanosaild.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/smallsats/nanosaild.html" rel="nofollow">NASA Mission Site for NanoSail-D</a></li>
<li><a href="http://memoryalpha.wikia.com/wiki/Solar_sail" class="external text" title="http://memoryalpha.wikia.com/wiki/Solar_sail" rel="nofollow">Solar sail</a> on <a href="http://memoryalpha.wikia.com/" class="external text" title="http://memoryalpha.wikia.com/" rel="nofollow">Memory Alpha: The Star Trek Wiki</a> (a <a href="/wiki/Star_Trek" title="Star Trek">Star Trek</a> <a href="/wiki/Wiki" title="Wiki">wiki</a>)</li>
<li><i>NanoSail-D</i> mission: Dana Coulter, <a href="http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/26jun_nanosaild.htm?list1097511" class="external text" title="http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/26jun_nanosaild.htm?list1097511" rel="nofollow">"NASA to Attempt Historic Solar Sail Deployment"</a>, NASA, June 28 2008</li>
<li><a href="http://www-spof.gsfc.nasa.gov/stargaze/Solsail.htm" class="external text" title="http://www-spof.gsfc.nasa.gov/stargaze/Solsail.htm" rel="nofollow">Far-out Pathways to Space: Solar Sails</a> from NASA</li>
<li><a href="http://www.solarsails.info" class="external text" title="http://www.solarsails.info" rel="nofollow">Solar Sails</a> Comprehensive collection of solar sail information and references, maintained by Benjamin Diedrich. Good diagrams<a href="http://wiki.solarsails.info/index.php?title=Tacking_Solar_Sails" class="external autonumber" title="http://wiki.solarsails.info/index.php?title=Tacking_Solar_Sails" rel="nofollow">[7]</a> showing how light sailors must tack.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.u3p.net/" class="external text" title="http://www.u3p.net/" rel="nofollow">U3P</a> Multilingual site with news and flight simulators</li>
<li><a href="http://www.isas.jaxa.jp/e/snews/2004/0809.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.isas.jaxa.jp/e/snews/2004/0809.shtml" rel="nofollow">ISAS Deployed Solar Sail Film in Space</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.planetary.org/programs/projects/solar_sailing/" class="external text" title="http://www.planetary.org/programs/projects/solar_sailing/" rel="nofollow">Planetary society site for solar sailing projects</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.solar-thruster-sailor.info/figs/fig13.html" class="external text" title="http://www.solar-thruster-sailor.info/figs/fig13.html" rel="nofollow">Suggestion of a solar sail with roller reefing, hybrid propulsion and a central docking and payload station.</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.andybrain.com/extras/solar-sail.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.andybrain.com/extras/solar-sail.htm" rel="nofollow">Interview with NASA's JPL about solar sail technology and missions</a></li>
<li><a href="http://nuke.giovannivulpetti.it/SolarSailing/tabid/56/Default.aspx" class="external text" title="http://nuke.giovannivulpetti.it/SolarSailing/tabid/56/Default.aspx" rel="nofollow">Website with technical pdf-files about solar-sailing, including NASA report and lectures at Aerospace Engineering School of Rome University</a></li>
<li><a href="http://72.14.253.104/search?q=cache:qwgqedUymfwJ:www.niac.usra.edu/files/studies/final_report/4Landis.pdf+physics+solar+sails+dopler+shift&amp;hl=en&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=41&amp;gl=us" class="external text" title="http://72.14.253.104/search?q=cache:qwgqedUymfwJ:www.niac.usra.edu/files/studies/final_report/4Landis.pdf+physics+solar+sails+dopler+shift&amp;hl=en&amp;ct=clnk&amp;cd=41&amp;gl=us" rel="nofollow">Advanced Solar- and Laser-pushed Lightsail Concepts</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFAndrews.2C_D.G.2009">Andrews, D.G. (2003). <a href="http://www.andrews-space.com/images/videos/PAPERS/Pub-InterstellarTransportation(200307).pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.andrews-space.com/images/videos/PAPERS/Pub-InterstellarTransportation(200307).pdf" rel="nofollow">"Interstellar Transportation using Today’s Physics"</a>. American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.andrews-space.com/images/videos/PAPERS/Pub-InterstellarTransportation(200307).pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.andrews-space.com/images/videos/PAPERS/Pub-InterstellarTransportation(200307).pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.andrews-space.com/images/videos/PAPERS/Pub-InterstellarTransportation(200307).pdf</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Interstellar+Transportation+using+Today%E2%80%99s+Physics&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Andrews%2C+D.G.&amp;rft.au=Andrews%2C+D.G.&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.pub=American+Institute+of+Aeronautics+and+Astronautics&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.andrews-space.com%2Fimages%2Fvideos%2FPAPERS%2FPub-InterstellarTransportation%28200307%29.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Solar_sail"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
